#Ad ☀️ Did you know that snow reflects up to 88% of the Sun’s UV rays, nearly doubling your exposure to harmful radiation? Plus UV rays are even stronger at higher elevations. A double hit on your skin if you’re planning on spending a day up in the mountains!

I’ve partnered with @neutrogenacanada and the @melanomanetwork to help promote proper sun protection by participating in the @7summits4skincancer Challenge. Join the virtual event with me and run, bike, skate, ski, snowshoe, or walk the combined total of the worlds tallest summits — 43.29KM! (or as many as you can) and raise funds and awareness for the @melanomanetwork

Hiking through the Scottish highlands with @seabourncruise! 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Knockan Crag is home to the birthplace of modern geology. Back in the 19th century, a cliff was discovered here that set the scientific world ablaze. Much older rock sits atop much younger ones, giving way to our current understanding of plate tectonics.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#SeabournCruise #SeabournPartner #Ad

Dunnottar castle is a medieval fortress, built on the rocky edge of Scotland. It played an important role in the history of Scotlands development due to its strategic location for people to come shoot bangers. 😉

During my unforgettable 12-day cruise around the enchanting Land of the Celts with @seabourncruise, every moment was filled with awe-inspiring experiences. 

I embarked on the magnificent Seabourn Venture, an expedition ship specially designed for thrilling zodiac operations and extraordinary shore excursions. It was the perfect vessel to explore the hidden gems of the UK’s Celtic regions. 

Starting in London we set sail to the picturesque Isle of Scilly, vibrant Dublin, historic Isle of Man, and captivating Glasgow. The mystical Isle of Iona and Staffa left me in awe, while the rugged beauty of Isle of Lewis and the charming town of Kirkwall added to the adventure. We concluded the sailing in Edinburgh. 

The days filled with exploration were followed by evenings of pure luxury and indulgence. From fine dining to world class entertainment, Seabourn provided unparalleled luxury and comfort. 

Seabourn single handedly shifted my perception of cruising for the better, delivering an experience that exceeded all expectations. I’m beyond grateful for this dream like journey, witnessing the beauty and heritage of the Celts and I can’t wait for the next adventure! #SeabournCruise #SeabournPartner #Ad

location.city_name: Calanais Standing Stones, Isle of Lewis

social_posts.post_text:
Check out this mind-blowing fact about the Calanais Standing Stones: they predate Stonehenge by a staggering 2000 years, and yet, we’re still puzzled about their purpose and origins! 🤯

The prevailing theory suggests they were some kind of ancient observatory, but here’s the twist. These colossal stones weigh a TON! The centre stone stands 4.8m tall. How were primitive humans able to achieve such feats without modern machinery, or mechanical advantage? 🤔

It makes you wonder if ancient humans were far more advanced than we currently give them credit for, or if they received some otherworldly assistance… what’s your take on this captivating mystery?

Grateful to witness such wonders alongside @seabourncruise 
#SeabournPartner #Ad
The invigorating power of the sauna, immersed in the breathtaking beauty of the open ocean, this was one of the coolest sauna’s I’ve ever used… 😌🌊 @seabourncruise #SeabournVenture
